OL,5,Cforgotten
OL,7,F"We have pressed the council for
OL,8,Finformation on their plans for the
OL,9,Ffuture of the site, and arrangements
OL,10,Ffor the commercial and residential
OL,11,Ftenants. We have not been supplied
OL,12,Fwith any answers or details of whom
OL,13,Ftenants should contact if they need
OL,14,Fto. Those tenants to whom we have
OL,15,Fspoken are not happy."
OL,17,FMr Sillifant added: "It is unfortunate
OL,18,Fthat an orderly transfer doesn't seem
OL,19,Fwithin our grasp."
